Their salads are also very delicious (when I say salad, I don't mean a lean version of an american tossed salad, these are rich and pretty filling salads), that I usually order as appetizer.

This place is amazing, definitely a gem in this neighborhood.  I came here with family and had Samsi, all types of Kebabs, and Plof. All the food was delicious and affordable. I couldn't get enough of the lamb rib kebabs with the red sauce.  We also had the great opportunity to come in when they had live music, made it a way more cultural experience.  As for the drinks, this place is BYOB with a liquor store nearby, just order some cranberry and orange juice and go wild.
I like the rice "Plov" and "Somsa" and Owner was also really nice guy I will come to eat "Kabob" next time
